casebody.data:
Finney vs. Hood et al.; Thurman vs. Culverhouse; Walker vs. Banks, trustee October 5, 11, 24, 1883.

After a bill of exceptions has been filed in the office of the clerk of the superior court, an acknowledgment of service by defendant in error cannot be endorsed thereon; and the writ will be dismissed, although such entry purports to acknowledge “due and legal service.”

Writ of error dismissed.
